                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.—Received August 30, 1900. Date
                        lost in transmission.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger reports that the Imperial palace will be entered August 28. Military
                    promenade of all nations will be made through it, after which it will be closed
                    and guarded. This action is necessary to forcibly impress the Chinese. More
                    Russian, German, Italian, and French troops are arriving. Prince Ching is
                    expected in a few days.</p>
                <p>Asks if Department has instructions for him.)</p>
            </div>
